      <abstract>
        <p>Roundup of recent advertising account changes (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>* E*Trade Securities, Menlo Park, Calif., to Admerasia, New York, to handle marketing aimed at Chinese-American consumers, including a new Chinese-language Web site at www.chinese.etrade.com. Billings were not disclosed.  * Time Warner Cable, Stamford, Conn., to the Romann Group, New York, as the first agency to handle strategic and creative work for a new video-on-demand cable service. Billings were estimated at $15 million.</p>
      </block>
